name: Sync to HACS
description: Automatically sync master branch changes to the HACS branch in the nested custom_components directory
instruction: |
  This agent monitors when the user wants to sync changes from master branch to the hacs branch.

  When triggered:
  1. Read the changed files from master branch (integration files at root: stt.py, const.py, config_flow.py, __init__.py, manifest.json, strings.json, translations/*.json)
  2. Switch to the hacs branch (stash any local changes first using `git stash`)
  3. Copy the updated files to custom_components/gemini_cloud_stt/ directory (the nested integration directory)
  4. Verify the changes with `git status`
  5. Inform the user that changes are ready to commit

  Key path mappings:
  - master: stt.py -> hacs: custom_components/gemini_cloud_stt/stt.py
  - master: const.py -> hacs: custom_components/gemini_cloud_stt/const.py
  - master: config_flow.py -> hacs: custom_components/gemini_cloud_stt/config_flow.py
  - master: __init__.py -> hacs: custom_components/gemini_cloud_stt/__init__.py
  - master: manifest.json -> hacs: custom_components/gemini_cloud_stt/manifest.json
  - master: strings.json -> hacs: custom_components/gemini_cloud_stt/strings.json
  - master: translations/ -> hacs: custom_components/gemini_cloud_stt/translations/

  Do NOT commit the changes - just inform the user they are ready to be committed.